could meet in their carriages

00:16:17.960 --> 00:16:23.960
and have flirtations with other
members of either the same sex

00:16:23.960 --> 00:16:26.450
or the opposite sex.

00:16:26.450 --> 00:16:28.200
Essentially, it was a--

00:16:28.200 --> 00:16:35.960
it took an idea of a street
as an environment for play

00:16:35.960 --> 00:16:43.785
and transformed it into another
version of the same idea.

00:16:46.450 --> 00:16:51.330
So the streets of Paris
played almost every role

00:16:51.330 --> 00:16:53.130
you can imagine.

00:16:53.130 --> 00:17:00.150
This is, linguistically,
an interesting reach,

00:17:00.150 --> 00:17:02.880
from closing a
street in Florence

00:17:02.880 --> 00:17:09.030
to play a game to use the
same word etymologically,

00:17:09.030 --> 00:17:10.980
now being used for--

00:17:10.980 --> 00:17:14.480
to describe an American
shopping center.

00:17:14.480 --> 00:17:15.520
Any connection?

