Perhaps the mall
became a general term,

00:17:30.960 --> 00:17:36.210
and the Americans picked it up
and applied it indiscriminantly

00:17:36.210 --> 00:17:37.890
of its origin.

00:17:37.890 --> 00:17:38.910
Absolutely.

00:17:45.300 --> 00:17:51.830
Well, the Romans crossed the
river, as they did in London,

00:17:51.830 --> 00:17:55.580
but found an island
about 20 acres large

00:17:55.580 --> 00:17:59.390
in the center of the river
which became the foundation

00:17:59.390 --> 00:18:03.320
of the city of Paris.

00:18:03.320 --> 00:18:13.030
The Romans stayed until
about the fifth century.

00:18:13.030 --> 00:18:15.280
One of the governors
of the Romans was--

00:18:15.280 --> 00:18:18.090
had my name.

00:18:18.090 --> 00:18:19.570
He was a cousin--

00:18:19.570 --> 00:18:23.340
he was a nephew of the
Emperor Constantine.

00:18:23.340 --> 00:18:26.980
He then became the last
of the Roman emperors.

00:18:26.980 --> 00:18:30.430
He was killed by his
own troops because he

00:18:30.430 --> 00:18:34.510
was unlike his uncle
or a Christian.

00:18:34.510 --> 00:18:39.190
He believed in stemming
the Christian epidemic

00:18:39.190 --> 00:18:46.300
and wanted Rome to remain in
touch with the Mithrian rights

00:18:46.300 --> 00:18:53.440
and multigods and systems
of religion, which was being

00:18:53.440 --> 00:18:55.540
sabotaged by Christianity.

00:19:01.840 --> 00:19:04.660
I'm just going to
go through some

00:19:04.660 --> 00:19:11.620
of the aspects of this spatial
system is put into place.

00:19:15.760 --> 00:19:26.390
Philippe August, 1180 to 1223,
built on the Ile de Cité,

00:19:26.390 --> 00:19:28.070
the island.

00:19:28.070 --> 00:19:33.020
He built a palace, the
beginning of the Louvre,

00:19:33.020 --> 00:19:40.720
the law courts, the bishop's
palace, Ile de Cite,

00:19:40.720 --> 00:19:43.330
all on the 20 acres.

00:19:43.330 --> 00:19:44.695
He built the second wall.

00:19:47.450 --> 00:19:53.540
He already agitated for the
rebuilding of Les Halles.

00:19:53.540 --> 00:19:58.030
Les Halles, the
land of Les Halles

00:19:58.030 --> 00:20:01.510
was developed and
occupied by Jews.

00:20:01.510 --> 00:20:04.630
In the 12th century,
it was common to be--

00:20:04.630 --> 00:20:10.700
for kings to be anti-Semitic.

00:20:10.700 --> 00:20:13.670
The Jews were expelled
from their property,

00:20:13.670 --> 00:20:16.490
and Les Halles was built.
So when you go to Les Halles

00:20:16.490 --> 00:20:19.850
today, which are now an
underground shopping center,

00:20:19.850 --> 00:20:25.470
you'll have to think back to
understand that it was land

00:20:25.470 --> 00:20:27.290
from which Jews were expelled.

00:20:27.290 --> 00:20:30.170
In England, at the
same time, Jews

00:20:30.170 --> 00:20:33.500
had to wear a badge
to show themselves as

00:20:33.500 --> 00:20:35.660
different from ordinary people.

00:20:35.660 --> 00:20:39.320
They had to pay tax when
they entered or left London.

00:20:39.320 --> 00:20:42.710
And Henry II, I think it was.

00:20:42.710 --> 00:20:51.110
So the behavior
of the French King

00:20:51.110 --> 00:20:56.980
was in sync, synchronized with
the behavior of his colleagues

00:20:56.980 --> 00:20:59.590
out in Europe.

00:20:59.590 --> 00:21:03.040
Notre Dame was built
in the 12th century.

00:21:03.040 --> 00:21:07.990
So centered is Paris in
the geography of France

00:21:07.990 --> 00:21:11.950
that, even today, all
measurements in France

00:21:11.950 --> 00:21:13.550
measured from Notre Dame.

00:21:17.960 --> 00:21:21.560
There isn't that sense of
centrality in the London.

00:21:24.490 --> 00:21:30.100
There were crowds gathered
to watch a hanging,

00:21:30.100 --> 00:21:32.800
but nothing like
the crowds which

00:21:32.800 --> 00:21:37.750
gathered to watch the guillotine
and to watch people be headed,

00:21:37.750 --> 00:21:40.000
to wath cats being fried.

00:21:48.900 --> 00:21:57.660
The great King Henry
IV, a 16th century king

00:21:57.660 --> 00:21:59.880
whose second wife
Marie de' Medici

00:21:59.880 --> 00:22:04.530
I've mentioned already in
relation to Cours la Reine,

00:22:04.530 --> 00:22:11.550
