central part of Paris, bridges,

00:22:11.550 --> 00:22:18.330
palaces, churches, gardens.

00:22:18.330 --> 00:22:20.250
He built the Pont Neuf.

00:22:20.250 --> 00:22:22.500
He also built the
Place Royale, which

00:22:22.500 --> 00:22:26.460
is the largest residential
square in Europe

00:22:26.460 --> 00:22:33.720
and the predictor of
the Covent Garden model.

00:22:33.720 --> 00:22:38.670
The Cours la Reine, at
least the Place Royale,

00:22:38.670 --> 00:22:41.940
which is now the
Place des Vosges,

00:22:41.940 --> 00:22:45.110
is 140 meters, if I
remember correctly,

00:22:45.110 --> 00:22:48.630
140 meters by 140 meters.

00:22:48.630 --> 00:22:53.910
It's the largest residential
public space in Europe,

00:22:53.910 --> 00:23:05.340
built as the residence for the
royalty and the aristocracy.

